resources.string: Ohio DevFest 2016 is a 100% community organized developer conference with industry experts presenting on exciting topics including mobile, web, cloud, virtual reality, machine learning, and more! Ohio DevFest 2016 is scheduled for November 19th, 2016 at the University of Cincinnati.

string.name: code_of_conduct_1
string.b: This “Don’t be a jerk” policy is a shortened, more casual version of the longer Code of Conduct policy. Read full version.

resources.string: The GDG communities organizing this event are open, respectful, and inclusive communities. That means jerky behavior isn’t allowed at GDG meetings or events. Because we know that it’s not obvious to everyone, here’s a reminder of the types of things we don’t allow: jokes or offensive comments about sex/sexuality/race/religion/nationality/age/disability/body size, showing porn in public, touching people uninvited, or continuing to interact with someone after they’ve asked you to stop. Continuous jerky behavior may result in getting expelled from the meeting, event, or GDG Chapter(s).
If someone is bothering you, please tell an organizer immediately and they will take care of it. We want to maintain GDG DevFest’s awesomeness.
Tickets grant access to all conference sessions, coffee breaks, and lunch. Accommodation is NOT included in the ticket price.

Ohio DevFest 2016​ welcomes businesses that are looking to increase their presence in the Ohio regional tech communities by reaching local developers and technology focused individuals through event sponsorships.
